access_key.name: Description
access_key.value:
The access key for API operations. You can retrieve this
from the 'Security & Credentials' section of the AWS console.

external_id.name: Description
external_id.value: The external ID to use when assuming the role. If omitted, no external ID is passed to the AssumeRole call.

policy.name: Description
policy.value: The permissions applied when assuming a role. You cannot use, this policy to grant further permissions that are in excess to those of the,  role that is being assumed.

role_arn.name: Description
role_arn.value: The ARN of an IAM role to assume prior to making API calls.

session_name.name: Description
session_name.value: The session name to use when assuming the role. If omitted, no session name is passed to the AssumeRole call.

dynamodb_endpoint.name: Description
dynamodb_endpoint.value:

It's typically used to connect to dynamodb-local.

max_retries.name: Description
max_retries.value:
The maximum number of times an AWS API request is
being executed. If the API request still fails, an error is
thrown.

profile.name: Description
profile.value:
The profile for API operations. If not set, the default profile
created with `aws configure` will be used.

region.name: Description
region.value:
The region where AWS operations will take place. Examples
are us-east-1, us-west-2, etc.

s3_force_path_style.name: Description
s3_force_path_style.value:
Set this to true to force the request to use path-style addressing,
i.e., http://s3.amazonaws.com/BUCKET/KEY. By default, the S3 client will
use virtual hosted bucket addressing when possible
(http://BUCKET.s3.amazonaws.com/KEY). Specific to the Amazon S3 service.

secret_key.name: Description
secret_key.value:
The secret key for API operations. You can retrieve this
from the 'Security & Credentials' section of the AWS console.

shared_credentials_file.name: Description
shared_credentials_file.value:
The path to the shared credentials file. If not set
this defaults to ~/.aws/credentials.

skip_credentials_validation.name: Description
skip_credentials_validation.value: Skip the credentials validation via STS API. Used for AWS API implementations that do not have STS available/implemented.

skip_get_ec2_platforms.name: Description
skip_get_ec2_platforms.value: Skip getting the supported EC2 platforms. Used by users that don't have ec2:DescribeAccountAttributes permissions.

skip_region_validation.name: Description
skip_region_validation.value: Skip static validation of region name. Used by users of alternative AWS-like APIs or users w/ access to regions that are not public (yet).

skip_requesting_account_id.name: Description
skip_requesting_account_id.value: Skip requesting the account ID. Used for AWS API implementations that do not have IAM/STS API and/or metadata API.

token.name: Description
token.value:
session token. A session token is only required if you are
using temporary security credentials.

stage_key.name: Deprecated
stage_key.value: Since the API Gateway usage plans feature was launched on August 11, 2016, usage plans are now required to associate an API key with an API stage

min_adjustment_step.name: Deprecated
min_adjustment_step.value: Use min_adjustment_magnitude instead, otherwise you may see a perpetual diff on this resource.

timeout.name: Removed
timeout.value: This field has been removed. Please use build_timeout instead

reference_name.name: Deprecated
reference_name.value: Please use attribute `creation_token' instead. This attribute might be removed in future releases.

secret.name: Deprecated
secret.value: Please use a PGP key to encrypt

roles.name: Deprecated
roles.value: Use `role` instead. Only a single role can be passed to an IAM Instance Profile

force_destroy.name: Description
force_destroy.value: Delete user even if it has non-Terraform-managed IAM access keys, login profile or MFA devices
